OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F367A1774811467
OL,3,CFarmer who allowed waste to be dumped
OL,4,Cand buried at beauty spot sentenced
OL,6,FA farmer has been sentenced for
OL,7,Fallowing thousands of tonnes of waste
OL,8,Fto be dumped and buried on his land.
OL,10,FHaydenn Fortune, 50, pleaded guilty to
OL,11,Foperating an illegal waste site on
OL,12,FPyethornes Farm in Skipton.
OL,14,FThe large-scale waste dump was first
OL,15,Freported to the Environment Agency in
OL,16,FMay 2024.
OL,18,FWhen officers attended they found the
OL,19,Fsmelly site had large amounts of
OL,20,Fshredded plastic, metals, electrical
OL,21,Fitems and aerosols.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G1/4
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
